You don't need to know anything about hardware or programming to join. We can show you how to build a robot in under an hour and would love to have you join us!

name: Blacks in Technology - Denver
description: The goal for Blacks In Technology Denver (BIT-Denver) is to create a vibrant community of like-minded African American technology professionals, innovators and enthusiasts who are working with or interested in Web-based and related technologies. We’re talking the whole techie gamut from bloggers, digital media specialists, community managers and web masters to web designers, social media strategists, developers, online marketing experts, recruiters, software developers and project managers. And of course the doors are wide open for those folks who are simply just passionate about all things technical. We will meet regularly at least once a month for fun socializing and high level talks on the technology topics. We plan to feature educational meetups to learn latest technical developments in fields of interest. We also look forward to hosting mashup events with many of the multitude of great tech groups based in Denver. We also plan to participate in local startup events and help bring together Denver-based developers and web entrepreneurs for possible business opportunities. We feel this will be an excellent venue to exchange ideas and talk about web technology, innovation, open source, share our knowledge and experience with one another. Tell us how technology is changing the world. Anyone interested in tech is welcome!

name: DevOps Boulder
description: Development and Operations, together as one. We are change managing the world, one great project at a time.

name: Denver Beers with Engineers
description: This is a casual meet up group for all interested in defining their organization's digital agenda. The EMC FEDERATION, EMC II, Pivotal, RSA, VCE, Virtustream and VMware, form a unique Federation of strategically aligned businesses, each focused and free to execute individually or together. The Federation provides customer solutions and choice for the software-defined enterprise and the emerging “3rd platform” of mobile, cloud, big data and social, transformed by billions of users and millions of apps. OR just join us to drink beer, talk some shop and get know the experts of EMCII, VMware, Pivotal, RSA, VCE and Virtustream in the Denver community. We will be featuring a technical expert from each one of the organizations monthly, so don't miss out on your chance to learn what's new, while sipping on a few brews. See you soon!

name: Boulder Area Tesla Coil Initiative
description:
The Initiative:

This is a meetup for people interested in collaborating together to learn and understand the many works of Nikola Tesla. We will dive into the different experiments and concepts from his Colorado Springs Notebook (1899-1900).

This is meant to initiate a collective of people interested in understanding how everything is already in vibration, and how we can tap into it. We will work together, help each other learn and understand these concepts from different points of view. 

We will bring different skill sets and backgrounds to arrive at a singular understanding of what Nikola Tesla's greatest discoveries were and the goals he had in mind. 

The Setting:

This will happen in a classroom setting at the University of Boulder - Colorado. We will have open discussions and questions as we move through the Colorado Springs Notebook. Electrical engineers are encouraged to come and critique the readings as we apply more conventional understandings to old science. 

The Challenge:

This is meant to be a challenge to Electrical Engineers/Conventional Physicists as we move through experiments that contradict the the teachings of conventional electromagnetic physics. This is in hopes of starting a group of people actively researching and rediscovering Tesla's lost discoveries to arrive at new understandings. 

Many of Tesla's ideas involved increasing Human Energy in the form of intelligence. This is the group's primary goal. Please come with an open mind as we dive into the unknown discoveries of Nikola Tesla.

name: Denver Deep Learning and Neural Networks Group
description:
This group is for anyone who is interested in Neural Networks and Deep Learning. In this group we will be sharing our experiences related to Deep Learning, Neural Networks, Machine Learning, Data analytics and Big data. The goal is to emerge as a group to bring awareness in community about Deep Learning and connect with people with similar interest in Deep Learning. The format of this meetup is very casual, and topics will be covered in Discussion formats rather than completely PowerPoint Presentation mode.

Feel free to propose topics to discuss related to Neural Networks and Deep Learning.

name: Denver Quickbooks Meetup
description: We are the Denver Metro Group of Woodard Network Group (formerly known as NAN National Adviser Networking Group). Our goal is to foster cooperation, support, referrals and learning among the many accounting professionals in our area. Members and guests will typically be ProAdvisors, CPAs, Bookkeepers and IT professionals. Meetings will include time for networking, presentation and discussion of issues that we each face in our businesses. Additionally we may invite a vendor representative or guest speaker to present their solutions so we may utilize them for the betterment of our clients businesses. Our meetings are held the 3rd Wednesday of each month from 4:30-6:00 in Centennial, CO.

name: Colorado Ceph Meetup
description: This is a group for anyone interested in Ceph ( http://ceph.com/ ). All skills levels are welcome. There is a growing user community around this Free Software distributed storage. Participants are expected to share their use cases, tips and tricks, projects, have a good time in a friendly and informal atmosphere.

name: ReactJS Denver
description: ReactJS Denver is focused on Facebook's ReactJS library and the technologies and architectures surrounding it. We welcome initiates, beginners, mid-level, and experts alike. This meetup is focused on sharing successes and failures in working with ReactJS and the backing stack. Come share stories, listen to talks, eat, drink, and be merry.

name: FME Colorado User Group
description: This meetup is for users of Safe Software's FME (Feature Manipulation Engine) products both desktop and server. We exchange tips, tricks, and techniques as well as socialize and exchange ideas. We will usually have a speaker.

name: Google Developer Group Boulder
description: Interested in Google’s developer technologies? Have an eye for Android, App Engine, or Google Chrome platforms? GDG Boulder is now up and running. Come by to meet some likeminded developers, talk tech with members of your community, and trade thoughts about all things Google. We may put together an API, we may have guest speakers, bring your ideas.

name: Big Data Developers in Denver
description:
This is an IBM sponsored Big Data meetup group.� Geared towards developers, data scientists and ALL Big Data enthusiasts, our meetups provide an opportunity to work hands on with the solutions and tools in our Big Data portfolio.
Our Meetups typically include a 45-60 min (max) presentation that serves as an introduction and overview for a specific Big Data technology.� It is followed by ~3 hours to collaborate with fellow developers and apply your Big Data skills.� We provide a cloud environment that you can run through the browser of your laptop at NO cost to you.� Our meetups are FREE.
Meetup topics include:
- Hadoop-based analytics
- Stream Computing
- Text Analytics
- Visualization and Discovery tools for Big Data
- Big Data App Development
- Deep dives into the technologies that makes big data processing possible
- Anything and everything about Big Data
Join us today for a hands on software development experience.

name: Boulder BBI Ethics Meetup
description: Social media offers an unprecedented set of opportunities and responsibilities for individuals and organizations. For individuals, social media offers new routes to self-expression mixed with shifting, sometimes unfamiliar expectations regarding ownership and privacy of that data. For organizations, social data offers new ways to glean insight into customer and consumer attitudes, emotions and behaviors down to the individual level, and therefore also raises ethical dilemmas with regard to direct use. This meetup will seek to generate more input for the authors of the draft code.

name: Denver Salesforce Developer Group
description: Connect with developers building on the Salesforce Platform

name: FullStackEvents - a meetup for #EventProfs in Colorado
description:
FullStackEvents is a quarterly gathering to support #eventprofs and #eventtech leaders who produce and promote conferences, tradeshows, festivals and sporting events across Colorado and beyond. 

We are unified by our love of crowds, industry tools and technology. 

We thrive on productivity and progress. 

We host interactive content from thought leaders in our industry who provide insights, stories and tips to improve our skills, grow our businesses and stay ahead of the competition. 

We are here to learn from each other, network and share ideas. 

We are committed to helping each other prosper in our industry and advance our careers. 

Together, we aim to shape the next wave of event innovation, community engagement and social change.

name: Colorado Cloud Foundry Meetup
description: In the cloud era, the application platform will be delivered as a service, often described as Platform as a Service (PaaS). PaaS makes it much easier to deploy, run and scale applications. Cloud Foundry is the industry’s Open PaaS and provides a choice of clouds, frameworks and application services. As an open source project, there is a broad community both contributing and supporting Cloud Foundry. This Meetup is dedicated to fostering community engagement, contribution support for Cloud Foundry in Colorado.  Follow this Meetup on Twitter:  @cocloudfoundry

name: Colorado Cassandra Meetup
description:
The Apache Cassandra™ Project develops a highly scalable second-generation distributed database, bringing together Dynamo's fully distributed design and Bigtable's ColumnFamily-based data model. This Apache Cassandra™ User Group is a highly awesome meetup group, bringing together cool people to talk about our favorite NoSQL implementation, Apache Cassandra™.

You can also connect with the community globally through our #SLACK channel to network, share knowledge, and learn from real-world users of Apache Cassandra™ and DataStax Enterprise. Click on the group headline at the top of the page to interact with all the meetup group members world-wide.

Are you interested in speaking at an upcoming Cassandra™ event at any of our groups? If so, sign up here!

name: Denver InfluxDB Meetup
description:
This is a group for people using or interested in 

InfluxDB, an open source distributed time series, metrics, and events database

. We'll have drinkups, hackfests, office hours, and talks about InfluxDB or things related to it. DevOps, data visualization, analytics, anomaly detection, distributed computing, and NoSQL database design are all fair game.

name: Broomfield New Technology Meetup
description: This group is dedicated to IT professionals; users & influencers. We will be discussing best practices, challenges, and product relevance. The discussions will be centered around IT as a service to the business. Creating more than just a cost center out of the IT Dept (ie Infrastructure, Cloud, security, Dev Ops, App Dev, Simplification, etc...)

name: Colorado Clean Technology Community
description:
In March 2014, David M. Talon, Founder of the Clean Technology Community put this organization on its' path for success. As of July 2016, we have over 650 members and we grow each week. This is where Colorado Clean Technology professionals relax, speak frankly, find great resources, and learn from each other as you take your company from pilot to production. 

Our partners span a wide range of companies and organizations in the Global  Clean Technology Ecosphere. These include accelerators, incubators, alternative funding sources , investors and industry leaders. Our purpose is to help our member companies define their path to success and prepare them with practical education, mentoring, and industry introductions for each step along that course. 

Join us at an upcoming event and see how you can participate and contribute to our mission.

name: Boulder Women in Machine Learning & Data Science
description:
This is the Boulder chapter of Women in Machine Learning and Data Science (WiMLDS). We aim to provide an inviting and educational community for women interested in data.

We host events which include talks by prominent data scientists, lightning talks, technical workshops and networking events. Our members include engineers, technologists, statisticians, students and many other professionals who work in data science or would like to transition into this field.

name: EdTech Meetup CO
description:
By bringing together educators, entrepreneurs, technologists, and education industry enthusiasts, EdTech Meetup CO seeks to create a collaborative space where people across sectors can work together to tackle challenges and explore meaningful solutions for the global opportunities in education.

EdTech Meetup CO was founded by Dan Carroll and Mark Philipps and inspired by the SF EduTech Meetup.  In 2014, a new organizer was required or this Meetup would be shut down.

In that void, Educelerate stepped in to save the group in parallel with its other local community organized Meetups in Chicago and the Twin Cities and Los Angeles.  In so doing, we strive to be good stewards of the legacy EdTech Meetup CO and to grow and develop it further into a rich ecosystem of entrepreneurs, investors and partners.

Just as EdTech Meetup CO offers the benefits of a membership based network, so does Educelerate with our website Educelerate.com and live Meetup streams via Google Hangouts On-Air.

Educelerate is a Delaware not for profit with no sponsors or owners or any agenda other than supporting education innovation.  Please follow us @Educelerate, visit our website at www.educelerate.com or send us an email at colorado@educelerate.com.

name: All Things API: REST, Cloud, Integrations, Mashups & SaaS
description:
This is an all-developer group dedicated to sharing, evangelizing and promoting the next big wave in technology: REST, Cloud, Integrations, Mashups & SaaS etc. We focus on issues with APIs such as security, management, integration etc. Also we discuss on how these technologies impact the different business units in an organization e.g how product management or IT changes when you're building or using APIs, REST, Cloud, Integrations, Mashups & SaaS apps.

Not in Denver? Check out our other Meetups!

• Sydney

• San Francisco, CA

• Barcelona

name: Denver Open Source Users Group
description: DOSUG is a free and open user group studying the applications of open source to business software development.

name: Rust Boulder/Denver
description:
Join our Slack channel: http://rust-boulder-denver.herokuapp.com/

Come learn about Mozilla's new programming language, Rust! We'll discuss anything and everything related to Rust: design and implementation, libraries, interesting projects, idioms and gotchas, or whatever else anyone is interested in. We have no set format or location yet, join early and help define how it should work!

name: The Denver/Boulder Linux Meetup Group
description:
Welcome,

This group is being set up so that all the Front Range Linux groups will have a free resource to connect with Linux users of all skills and abilities.  Whether you are a Linux Guru, or just learning join feel free to join our group and meet other like minded users.  Regardless of your favorite distro, it is hoped that by making it easier or Linux users to come together, a better computing experience can be had by all.

And, if you are a Windows users and just curious about Linux, don't feel that you are not welcome to drop on by also.  If anything, the Linux community is always willing to embrace you, and help you learn our ways

name: DenMARK - Denver MarkLogic User's Group
description: This group is for folks in the Denver area interested in getting together to discuss MarkLogic and MarkLogic-related technologies.

name: CommercialTribe Engineering Networking
description:
If you’re interested in hanging with some cool, talented Developers and Engineers from one of Denver’s hottest startups, then join us for fun, food, drink, and talk on all things lean/agile software development, WebRTC, Mean stack, AWS and more!

And we’re hiring so bring a resume if you’re interested in joining our team.

We’re looking for people who want to go home and say, ‘I help companies improve their sales performance by enabling their sales reps to practice.’ We’re working toward a single goal – help sales achieve more – and the best members of the team are those that get excited at breaking the status quo for learning. It takes a close tribe to reach that goal, and we welcome those who want to help us transform sales.”

name: Cloudegy - The Cloud Community with a Strategy
description:
We are Cloudegy Denver. We are headed to the Cloud together.
Whether you're a cloud evangelist or committed to having the last completely private data center standing, we're all headed to the cloud in one way or another. Innovative business leaders in Denver who are committed to solving real business problems with cloud technologies know that Cloudegy is a place where you can learn and strategize with peers. We recognize that on-premise and hybrid solutions have their places and that each of you need to make informed decisions for optimal experiences for your constituent users and your organization's unique needs. We're here to help. None of us knows all the answers. So every few months our Cloudegy sponsors host an immersive experience for a limited number of attendees in a hands-on walk through of industry leading cloud solutions.

We're not talking about just a PowerPoint and some smoke and mirrors. Cloudegy is an intensive forum where innovators come to expand their knowledge and experience beyond the limits of the tools they've already deployed back at the office. At a Cloudegy immersion event, you will have the opportunity to get hands on experience with the latest cloud technologies that you've been hearing about. You can get your hands on the tools in a group setting where you can discuss how to solve the problems you are facing today with subject matter experts and peer users.

name: The Gizmo Dojo (Broomfield Makerspace)
description:
Visit our website, TheGizmoDojo.com and support our Kickstarter!!

We are trying to create a fun and welcoming place to come together and bring fantastic creations to life. Some of our meetups have included learning about Arduino, knitting, sewing, 3D printers, and Linux, making crepe paper roses, chainmaille, and jewelry, and working on a CNC router, as well as attending Maker Faires all over Colorado and visiting with our neighbor makerspaces. We are currently hanging out at the Broomfield Library and at a garage in Northglenn, but we are hunting for an affordable space we can rent.

The communities built around makerspaces are typically filled with makers with many different fields of expertise. That expertise is shared among the members through classes and workshops, as well as through informal hangouts. Makers themselves come in many shapes and sizes, and makers may not even know they are makers until they are given the opportunity to create something! Lots of Makerspaces are home to entrepreneurs who are starting their own businesses creating brand new products. The community will include makers from all ages and capabilities, all sharing the common goal of wanting to have fun and make things.

Spread the word, get excited, and start making things!

name: denhac - The Denver Hackerspace
description:
Denhac is a non-profit hackerspace founded in 2008. Er, wait, what’s a hackerspace? Hackerspaces are simply places for people to learn, work on tech projects, socialize and collaborate. Denhac offers a community space for classes and events, anywhere from lock picking to information security, to hardware hacking. We are open to the public any Tuesday after 8pm, and most Saturdays for classes and events.

check out http://denhac.org for our full schedule

Have a group, class or event? We're happy to host!

name: Denver Cloud Security Alliance Meetup
description:
Cloud is here to stay. Every single person reading this is a stakeholder in Cloud Security. What are the best practices for protecting gelatinous data flowing everywhere and anywhere? Come join the discussion. We try to have these conversations in the afternoon followed by a chance to relax at a nearby watering hole.

Here's more info:

Intention of this Meetup: promote Cloud Security awareness.  Build a Colorado community of security and compliance folks with an interest in protecting their organizations' cloud assets.  Meet periodically.

Requirements: cloud security is an emerging topic, and everybody's got info in the cloud, so the only requirement is to bring a good attitude, a healthy curiosity, and a willingness to share.  Obviously you must be 21 if we go get drinks afterwards.

Affiliations: the Colorado Cloud Security Alliance is affiliated with the Cloud Security Alliance.  Members tend to participate in ISSA, ISACA, and OWASP groups in Colorado although we are not affiliated with those groups.

Expectations: bring your sense of humor to discuss some very serious topics.  Save any "holy war" debates until after the preso.

name: Boulder/Denver BigData Meetup
description:
Come learn and/or share your experiences with NoSQL & Big Data technologies. No experience required.

BDBDUG Mission:

    To educate the Boulder/Denver community about emerging Big Data Technologies

BDBDUG Goals:

    Education: Introduce and educate the community about new and innovative Big Data Technologies

    Networking: Provide a forum for people interested in Big Data to network

    Hiring: Connect people looking for Big Data work with those hiring

    Technology Balance: Provide the proper level of vendor presentations so that when people decide to rely on Big Data they know their options for support

    Consistency: Consistency in meetup. Keep to a regular cadance with the meetups as well as time of month ( 3rd is wednesday at 6:00 PM )

    Economic Growth: Contribute to strenghening the Colorado economy and US competitiveness in the global marketplace

Sincerely - Andy, Brett, Dan

name: Boulder Data Science
description:
Hands-on project-oriented data science, with a heavy focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence. We're here to get neck-deep into projects and actually do awesome things!

Founded by Steven Rouk in November 2015, Boulder Data Science is a partner group to the Colorado Data Science Meetup which is based in Denver. Huge thanks to Galvanize and Graham McBain for their support, and for the inspiration for this group.

name: Denver Swift Heads
description:
Love Apple's new programming language Swift? Want to learn about the latest and greatest Swift (iOS, OS/X, tvOS, watchOS)? Have something you built via Swift that you wanna show off to your peers? Are you a Swift Novice? Are you a functional Swift expert? Then you've come to the right place. Join us at Denver Swift Heads. All skill levels are welcome.

Denver Swift Heads Code of Conduct

The Denver Swift Heads Meetup series allows developers and students to teach one another lessons learned. We strive to work together to encourage and engage all skill-levels.

(1) We are committed to making participation in this Meetup an open and inviting experience for everyone, regardless of level of experience, gender, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation, disability, personal appearance, body size, race, ethnicity, age, religion, or nationality. We are dedicated to ensuring a safe space for all peoples.

(2) We understand the value of finding members employment opportunities. To that effect, Recruiters may contact the Meetup organizers with your information and we will connect you with members seeking opportunities. We ask that everyone observe these channels and we will do our part to unite you with the perfect candidate.

(3) By adopting this Code of Conduct, Meetup members commit themselves to fairly and consistently applying these principles to every aspect of this Meetup. Members who do not follow or enforce the Code of Conduct may be permanently removed from the group. 

This Code of Conduct applies both within the physical Meetup location and online spaces when an individual is representing the project or its community.

So in other words, be nice and be cool.

name: OSM Colorado
description:
OpenStreetMap (OSM) Colorado is a local collaboration of people interested in contributing their efforts to create free maps. We encourage all of our mappers to organize or suggest mapping events throughout Colorado. Meetup activities can be simple social mixers, OSM basic to advanced training, or community mapping parties, which may include: hiking, skiing, mapping an entire town, and more. We also work with other groups on mapping, GIS and volunteer projects.

OpenStreetMap is a collaborative and world-wide community of more than 1,000,000 mappers who are working together to build a free street level map of the world.

If you are new to OSM, visit the New Mappers page.

name: Denver / Boulder Cloud Computing Group
description: Amazon AWS, Google, Rackspace Cloud, GoGrid Microsoft Azure, VMware, enStratus, RightScale... the list goes on and on. Cloud computing is changing the way we work and reshaping the way we manage and run companies. From startups to enterprises, it is disrupting the IT landscape. Come discuss how these Web products and services flatten the competitive landscape, and allow your business to put a ceiling on your costs while removing the ceiling from your growth.

name: Denver Microservices
description: We are a community of like minded software engineers that come together to decouple monolithic and spaghetti architectures. Microservices architecture is enabled by a spectrum of tools categories but is primarily an architectural approach to system design that also requires considerable organizational and cultural adjustment to execute successfully. This meetup is for people interested in architecting, designing, deploying and maintaining microservice based architectures.

name: Louisville Laravel Meetup
description: Find out why Laravel is the most popular PHP framework in 2014. This group is for all web developers and enthusiasts: beginners, experts and everyone in between. Learn how Laravel can help you enjoy producing professional MVC web applications.

name: Disruption and Chaos: Everything Must Change
description:
“Join a group of Technical Professionals in the Front Range focused on moving towards cloud native applications using EMC, VMWare and Pivotal technologies as a focal point of your journey!"

Agile organizations require cultural and technological shifts to build efficiency.  The Federation of EMC Companies plans to lead the march towards cloud native applications leveraging tools from virtualization, containers, cloud foundry, and HADOOP. Integrating next generation technologies allows creative flexibility to define the future.

name: Denver Mobile Development User Group
description:
This is a user group that focuses on mobile application and mobile web development. Each week a new speaker will present on a topic, technology, or other innovation relevant to getting started with or sharpening your skills for mobile development. Developers, students, networkers, entrepreneurs, and sponsors in the mobile space are encouraged to attend and learn something new about Mobile Development at each meet up.

The group meets every third Thursday at the Westminster College Hill Library at the Westminster Community College Campus. Each week there will be a meet and greet, a presentation, and things will wrap up with promotions or other giveaways provided by both the group and its sponsors. See you there!

name: Boulder/Denver D3.js and Data Visualization
description: This is a group for everyone interested in the art and science of data visualization, with a focus on using the d3.js JavaScript library. All skill levels welcome! This will be a monthly meetup with presentations and workshops on visualization techniques and tools, getting down to the nuts and bolts of code and design.

name: Colorado Drupal Meetups
description: Meet with others in your local area interested in building and strengthening the Drupal Community. Discuss new and exciting Drupal-related news - or just socialize with like-minded people!

name: Front Range Pythoneers
description:
About Us
Front Range Pythoneers are an active Python users group meeting in Denver and Boulder, Colorado, USA.

Activities
We meet on the 3rd Tuesday of the month at lunch time to learn from talks about Python topics, to swap stories and coding tips, and to enjoy food and drink. But we don't just talk about Python, we live it: on the first Saturday of most months, we get together for a code sprint. Front Range Pythoneers are proud to have contributed as a group to TurboGears2, Jython, Django, and IPython.

Join us! Whether you're just learning Python or have already memorized the output of "import this", you'll find something worthwhile.

The Mailing List and Wiki
Please join our mailing list at http://lists.community.tummy.com/mailman/listinfo/frpytho... and visit our main Python Wiki page at http://wiki.python.org/moin/FrontRangePythoneers for more information about Front Range Pythoneers.

name: RMOUG Meetup
description:
This meetup is fueled by the enthusiasm and varied interests of Rocky Mountain Oracle Users Group (RMOUG) members. We gather to talk about all topics relating to Oracle and other technologies too. RMOUG, based on the Front Range in the beautiful state of Colorado provides educational opportunities to members.

Membership to this is meetup is not restricted to RMOUG members.  If you have an interest in any or all things Oracle, you should consider the benefits of joining RMOUG.

Become part of our conversation....

name: DevOpsDays - Rockies
description:
DevOpsDays is a technical conference and group, aimed at developers, sysadmins and anyone else involved in technology, whether expert or beginner.

Truth is, agile techniques used in development have an impact on the way operations organizes its work. Similarly, operations and sysadmins are becoming programmers because of the virtualization and automation trend where everything is managed through an API.

We’re excited to help bring this fantastic event to the Rocky Mountain region April 23 & 24, 2015.

name: Denver Emacs Meetup
description: A meetup group dedicated to Emacs, a text editor over 35 years old and still going strong! We are a group to meet, hang out, and discuss various Emacs-related topics. Looking forward to seeing how everybody uses Emacs and sharing our own useful tidbits! See http://writequit.org/denver-emacs/ for more info.

name: Information Builders Denver Big Data & Analytics Meetup
description: Join us to discuss all things related to data - latest trends in predictive analytics, big data and general issues on challenges of access & management of your best data assets. Ideal members will be business and tech users in Denver Area companies who want to come together to share ideas and help define best practices Meetings are free of charge. Join us to share ideas, learn, network and have fun!

name: Computer Doc - OPEN HOUSE
description:
We just opened a new retail store front, with lots of room to host meetups.

We Will have several electronic and soldering stations. Additionally, we also have many electronics kits that you can purchase and build on site.

We will also be going over computers and networking. Anyone interested in learning about or needs help with electronics we feel it would be a great meet up for you or anyone else that would like to learn more about it.

name: Denver Google for Work Meetup
description: The Denver Google for Work Meetup Group is an informal group focused on developing relationships, exchanging ideas, and fostering cloud innovation, specifically in and around Google. We want to provide an open, comfortable environment for cloud computers and newcomers alike to meet and discuss related news, best practices, tips and anything else that might arise in this exciting and rapidly evolving technology niche. We welcome people from all backgrounds, not just IT, to come learn and network in the community. Whether you are already Google Evangelist, just getting started, or hearing about Google for Work for the first time, we want your participation!

name: Front Range NLP (Natural Language Processing)
description: This group is for people along the Colorado Front Range who are interested in the real NLP, i.e. Natural Language Processing. Topics may include (but are not limited to) computational linguistics, machine learning, information retrieval, and text analytics. If you are actively involved in NLP or just want to learn more, please join us.

name: Future of Data: Denver
description: This meetup is focused on the Future of Data and the open community data projects governed by the Apache Software Foundation. Geared towards developers, data scientists and ALL Data enthusiasts who are building modern data applications. Our meetups cover all data -- data-in-motion and data-at-rest. Meetups provide an opportunity to listen, share and work hands on with other technologists in the open source and open community Apache tools.

name: DTC Go (Programming Language) Meetup
description:
If you want to learn or share your experiences or explore more about Go language, please join us over beer and pizza. Here are some resources you might want to check if you are new to Go:

First you should take the language tour: http://tour.golang.org/
Then, you should visit:
- https://golang.org/doc/code.html To learn how to organize your Go workspace
- https://golang.org/doc/effective_go.html which would help you be more effective at writing Go
- https://golang.org/ref/spec will help you learn more about the language itself
- https://golang.org/doc/#articles For a lot more reading material

There are some awesome websites as well:
- https://blog.gopheracademy.com Well great resources for Gophers in general
- http://gotime.fm For a weekly podcast of Go awesomeness
- https://gobyexample.com If you are looking for examples of how to do things in Go
- http://go-database-sql.org If you are looking for how to use SQL databases in Go
- http://gophervids.appspot.com For a list of Go related videos from various authors

Finally, https://github.com/golang/go/wiki#learning-more-about-go will give a list of more resources to learn Go

name: Denver Mesos User Group
description: This is the Denver-area group for Apache Mesos. We will cover topics related to distributed systems with the key focus being Apache Mesos. Topics will include running Mesos (on-premise or in the Cloud), building infrastructures with Mesos, data processing with Apache Spark, technologies in the growing Mesos ecosystem, building custom schedulers and more.

name: Denver Oracle Developers
description: This is a group for anyone (Developers, Architects - System/Platform, Project Managers, etc) working with Oracle related technologies. This groups is and will always be a place that Oracle professionals seek solutions for the problems and challenges they are facing in the Cloud (SaaS, PaaS and IaaS) as a platform. Attend this meetup to learn what's new and exciting, what is going on in Oracle Cloud Platform & Technology. Share your thoughts, existing projects and/or upcoming initiatives where you can use Oracle Cloud Technologies. Share your thoughts & opinions too while you're at it, something everyone including folks at Oracle can learn. Nibbles and drinks will be provided. [P.S:- This web-site should not be used for job postings and we will keep sales pitches to the minimum. :)]

name: Colorado Enterprise IoT Professionals
description: A group to bring together individuals working with the internet of things. Looking to share and contribute about our experiences working on the cutting edge of technology and the challenges that we face at the enterprise level within large organizations. IoT crosses many disciplines and how do we build reliability and scalability into all aspects of our organization from mechanical to mobile applications and everything in between (firmware, embedded systems, QA, Project Planning, etc.). A forum also to talk and meet peers in this field. Group members encouraged to define what other topics and construct of future events.

name: Boulder Geek Jam Session
description: We are a group of hard-core techies who also like to jam. We've been casually gathering monthly for impromptu jam sessions in the Gorilla Logic office on Pearl Street and recently decided that we wanted to open up the space and the music-making opportunity to all our Boulder (and other nearby) neighbors who wish to join and collaborate on some good music, geek talk, and drinks/food. We've got all the gear: instruments, speakers, recording capabilities, (and other nerdy, super techie and geeky gadgets) to make it a fun time, guaranteed--now all we need is YOU!

name: Software Freedom School in Denver
description:
the Software Freedom School exists to teach the world how to use and why to choose free software.

David L. Willson and Heather L. Willson started SFS in 2013 to help teach the world free software and to feed the whole student, mind (techie classes), body (delicious food), and spirit (libre software).  We host Software Freedom First Saturday at the SFS HQ or Englewood Public Library: From 11am - 3pm you can learn about free software.

There are other events throughout the month and activities you can become involved in: Linux Camp and Study Groups to name a couple.

Our ideal members, via Meetup, are people, just like you, looking to learn more about freedom in the software community.  It could be a new graduate, a person looking to change careers, someone who is super savvy but has been using the proprietary software for too long! 

We are a community based company in the Denver area. We want to partner with hacker-spaces, maker-spaces, LUG's, small businesses, entrepreneurs, and small, free schools like us.  Our goal is to teach the world how to use and why to choose free software and it would be wonderful if you joined us!

We look forward to meeting you and are excited for you to be part of the libre community!

name: Apache Apex Next Gen Native Hadoop Big Data, Denver Chapter
description:
Welcome BigFoots!

This meetup has been formed to discuss customer use cases and design patterns related to Apache Apex, a next generation native Hadoop big data platform. We will build an Apex community that meets face to face in Denver. We expect this community to have a strong influence on the big data eco-system.

Apex unifies stream and batch processing. Use cases include ingestion, fast real-time analytics, data movement, disastor recovery in Hadoop, ETL, fast batch, alerts and real-time actions. Apex is a YARN native platform. It simplifies development and productization of Hadoop applications by reducing time to market. Key features include Enterprise Grade Operability with Fault Tolerance, State Management, Event Processing Guarantees, No Data Loss, High Performance, Linear Scalability. Apex enables users to run any user defined code natively in Hadoop. Apex comes with versioned webservice & metrics for system and application monitoring. Apex includes Malhar library of reusable operators (functions). Examples of connectors include the following

• Messaging Systems: ActiveMQ, Flume, JMS, Kafka, Kinesis Streams, MapR Streams, Nifi, RabbitMQ, Solace, ZeroMQ, etc.

• File Systems: HDFS, NFS, S3, etc.

• Databases/Stores: Accumulo, AeroSpike, Cassandra, CouchDb, MongoDB, HBase, Couchbase, Geode, HBase, Hive Tables, Impala, JDBC, HP Vertica, MemCache, MemSql, MySql, Oracle, Redis,  etc.

• Protocols: AMPQ, HTTP, FTP/SFTP, MQTT, SMTP, Rest/Soap, Twitter, Websockets, etc.

• Other Systems: Elastic Search, Solr, Twitter, etc. 

Our events will include production customer who will present their use cases. Customers use cases include internet of things, financial technologies, ad-tech, telecommunications, healthcare, automobiles, etc. 

If you are interested in helping organize (hosting, presenting, community leadership) Next Generation Native Hadoop Big Data Ingestion, Transform, and Egression Community, using Apex, please email apex-meetup@datatorrent.com.

We are looking forward to active contribution from you to build this meetup into a strong influence on big data eco-system. 

Thanks for joining. 

Apache Apex Community Organizer

name: Boulder Geo Meetup
description: The Boulder Geo Meetup aims to bring together geo professionals, developers, and students all interested in geospatial technologies.  We will host regular events that showcase innovative geospatial projects that are happening in our backyard.

name: Denver IBM Bluemix Meetup
description:
Hold on to your seats -- Bluemix is the "coolest" development/deployment environment to hit IT ... so ... we'll see what amount of response we get -- and then we will decide on a date and venue -- let's get ready to rock Denver!!

Geared towards developers, architects and all Bluemix enthusiasts, we learn about Bluemix hands on with fellow developers. Learn how to use this new PaaS product with the current apps. Our meetups are free and sponsored by IBM and our key partners.

We will focus on Bluemix applications and offerings as well as the new IBM Watson Platform Services that are accessible on Bluemix. The IBM Watson Platform Services, at least for the remainder of 2014, include user profiling, message resonance and relationship extraction services. Additionally, IBM has made Watson available for the Healthcare and Travel domains. 

Get started with  your own free Bluemix account here!  

Here is a great introduction to Bluemix:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OD1NP-Yk2BI

Some other links of interest:

•  IBM Watson Developer Cloud

name: Women Who Go Boulder
description: Women Who Go Boulder is the Boulder chapter of Women Who Go. We are women of the Go community. We hope that this group will provide a better entry point for women who are interested in Go. In sum, this group is for you if: 1. You identify as female, publicly or privately 2. You have some interest in Go

name: Denver Cumulus Linux and Open Networking Meetup
description:
Meet other developers and ops engineers using Cumulus Networks software and/or open networking solutions. Meet new friends, share ideas, provide feedback, become a champion and community leader. Talk about open networking and all of the cool new ideas surrounding it.

Cumulus Networks simplifies data center operations by delivering operating systems that run on industry standard Ethernet switches, merging networking into the architectural and supply chain model of compute and leveraging hundreds of existing management, automation and monitoring tools.

Learn more about Cumulus Networks software solutions at http://cumulusnetworks.com/products/

Learn more about the Technology Ecosystem at http://cumulusnetworks.com/solutions/

Join the Cumulus Networks Community at https://community.cumulusnetworks.com/cumulus

name: Denver DevOps Meetup
description: Where Development and Operations come together. A Denver based meet up for the SysAdmin/DevOps community.

name: Analytics.Club Boulder
description:
Analytics.CLUB is world’s largest data analytics community, sharing networking opportunities with other data-driven professionals and bringing “Analytics to the 99%”.

Where are your interests? Let our community help you find the resources you need. Join Analytics.CLUB to use the following online/offline programs.

Physical Monthly Networking Event

name: Bluemix - Boulder PaaS and Cloud Computing Meetup
description:
Welcome!  We are excited to be launching this MeetUp, and planning our first gathering!  

In the meantime, you can get started registering for Bluemix, for free, here:  https://ibm.biz/Meetup_Boulder  !

This is an IBM sponsored PaaS meetup group. Geared towards developers, architects and all Cloud Foundry and Bluemix enthusiasts.  We learn about and discuss emerging Industry and IBM "Points Of View" (PoVs).  We experience Bluemix hands-on with fellow developers.  And we have fun along the way ;-).  Our meetups are free.

Feel free to contact Madeline for more information.

name: Elastic Denver User Group
description:
This group is for anyone interested in open source search, logging, analytics & data visualization. We primarily focus on these open source projects — Elasticsearch, Kibana, Logstash, and Beats — but we welcome talks on any aspect of data exploration.

This Meetup community adheres to the Elastic Code of Conduct - https://www.elastic.co/community/codeofconduct. Attendance to events run as part of this Meetup group means you agree to be an awesome human and engage by these rules

name: Graph Nerds of Boulder
description: Do you look at the world as nodes and edges? Does Big Data make you salivate a little? We are getting together to discuss the latest in graph databases, modeling, libraries, data sets, and analysis. People wanting to discuss inner/outer joins need not apply.

name: Colorado Grav CMS Users
description:
Grav is not your average content management system. It's an open source, flat-file NoDB CMS written for PHP 5.5.9+ that is focused on being crazy fast, easy to learn and use, with powerful features to enable it be easily extended.

Content is just simple markdown files in folders, with no complicated databases to deal with. A powerful API and extensive hooks allow for plugins to extend Grav and a comprehensive package manager provides easy installation and updating of extensions. Flexible Twig templating allows easy realization of your designs.

• Homepage: http://getgrav.org

• GitHub: https://github.com/getgrav/grav

• Twitter: https://twitter.com/getgrav

• Forum: http://getgrav.org/forum

• Live Chat: https://gitter.im/getgrav/grav

Do you want to learn how to build a high performance and flexible website faster than you thought possible? Grav CMS is a new open source PHP platform that is growing quickly and attracting converts from traditional CMS platforms that are slow and cumbersome. Find out about Grav, what it offers, and discuss its use among like minded web professionals.

<br>

<br>

name: Denver Open Source OS Meetup
description:
All about open source operating systems. Want to discuss what's new in Linux? Fascinated by DragonflyBSD? In love with OpenWRT on the arduino yum? This is the group for you.

Each meeting will feature both open discussion, social time, and a presentation about a current topic or trend in operating systems.

Beginners and experienced users alike are welcome. The neckbeard percentage will be kept to a minimum

name: Q Review Denver
description:
Listen, learn, and interact with your peers about all things QlikView!
This event consists of technology professionals looking to engage each other in the sharing of development, implementation, and adoption best-practices.

name: Denver DevOps Networking Meetup
description: Do you want to deliver software projects faster and with greater efficiency? If so, you are not alone. Many teams are tripped up by manual deployments, inconsistent environments, and slow hand-offs. We will lead a discussion bringing together experts from Industry Thought Leaders, partners, customers and others to discuss DevOps approaches for delivering continuous innovation.

name: Denver Machine Learners
description: Modern machine learning algorithms like Support Vector Machine, Random Forest and Neural Nets are producing very promising results on large scale datasets. However understanding what is happening inside the black box and the nuanced differences of various implementations can be challenging. Topics and presentations will include open source tools, real-world case studies and an occasional talk by a theorist Ultimately a group to discuss all things Machine Learning! Topics may include (but are not limited to): learning theory, computer vision, natural language processing, data mining, computer audition, etc. Everyone is welcome!

name: MaptimeMileHigh
description:
MaptimeMileHigh is a map hack night for the greater Denver area. We meet regularly to work on maps, learn about geospatial data, and teach each other the latest cartographic tools. Maptime is, rather literally, time for mapmaking. Our mission is to open the doors of cartographic possibility to anyone interested by creating a time and space for collaborative learning, exploration, and map creation using mapping tools and technologies.

This open learning environment for all levels and degrees of knowledge offers intentional support for the beginner. Maptime is simultaneously flexible and structured, creating space for workshops, ongoing projects with a shared goal, and independent/collaborative work time. Inspiration for Maptime comes from both hack nights and knitting circles. Both are models of spaces for people to create and learn together. Our goal is to provide this space with an open heart and without pretension. You can bring your own projects to work on, or just hang out and socialize or ask questions. Some people are experts, and some people are just getting started, but all of us are learning, so why not do it together? 

Maptime is hands-on, so don't forget to bring your laptop! All skill levels are welcome. Newbies are especially welcome! Check out our site at maptime.io/milehigh and follow us on twitter @MaptimeMileHigh. If you're new to the group, check out our intro presentation.

MaptimeMileHigh is a local chapter of the world-wide Maptime movement! Check out Maptime HQ at maptime.io.

name: Maptime Boulder
description: What is Maptime, In the words of Lyzi Diamond, she states: "Maptime is a collection of beginner-focused community groups for learning geospatial technology, techniques, and concepts, particularly using open source tools and hands-on practice and exercises." So #Maptime Boulder, will be no different, we will seek to teach and learn from each other about the ever evolving world of all things GIS and maps! For more information go to: http://www.maptime.io/

name: GDG Denver
description:
The Google Developer Group Denver (GDG Denver) brings together experts, beginners and enthusiasts alike to meet and discuss a wide array of topics related to Google technologies. We hold the occasional programming event, and we get involved in Google developer challenge events. We strive to bring high quality speakers to share expertise about Google related technology with our group. Our goal is to hold meetings in or around downtown Denver. Disclaimer: GDG Denver is an independent group; our activities and the opinions expressed here should in no way be linked to Google, the corporation.

If you are interested in speaking at a future GDG event please fill out speaker form here: bit.ly/gdgdenverspeaker

name: Meteor Denver
description: Meet other developers using Meteor. Share your knowledge, apps, and get feedback from others. Meteor is an open-source platform for building top-quality web apps in a fraction of the time, whether you're an expert developer or just getting started.
